38
00:03:20,563 --> 00:03:22,649
So with something
that incredible going on,

39
00:03:22,774 --> 00:03:26,862
it should've started off with loads
of great things happening for me,

40
00:03:26,946 --> 00:03:29,032
but it didn't.

41
00:03:29,115 --> 00:03:33,454
I was from another state,
and I didn't have a single
friend in a thousand miles.

42
00:03:34,789 --> 00:03:37,209
It was a lousy way
to end up the fifth grade,

43
00:03:37,293 --> 00:03:40,422
'cause I had zip time
to make friends before summer.

44
00:03:40,505 --> 00:03:44,385
And that's about
where it all started.

45
00:03:48,599 --> 00:03:51,853
My real dad died
when I was just a little kid.

46
00:03:51,978 --> 00:03:56,401
My mom had married Bill about a year
before we moved to the Valley.

47
00:03:56,526 --> 00:04:01,449
At the time, he and I were still
getting used to each other.

48
00:04:01,574 --> 00:04:04,244
- [ Knocking ]
- Yeah.

49
00:04:06,122 --> 00:04:09,251
- Um, Dad?
- Mm-hm m?

50
00:04:09,292 --> 00:04:11,253
I -I mean Bill.

51
00:04:11,337 --> 00:04:16,260
- Remember you-- you promised
you'd teach me to play catch?
- Mm-hmm.

52
00:04:16,343 --> 00:04:18,554
Um,

53
00:04:18,638 --> 00:04:20,557
w-well,
