54
00:04:21,684 --> 00:04:24,270
Yeah. Sure.

55
00:04:30,445 --> 00:04:32,364
Okay.

56
00:04:32,447 --> 00:04:34,700
- Okay?
- Thanks.

57
00:04:40,458 --> 00:04:42,335
Sorry.

58
00:05:24,223 --> 00:05:27,519
[Man Narrating] I'd followed them
to the sandlot once after school.

59
00:05:27,602 --> 00:05:30,147
- I'd never seen any place like it.
- [ Boys Shouting ]

60
00:05:30,314 --> 00:05:33,276
It was like their own little
baseball kingdom or something.

61
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:36,239
It was the greatest place
I'd ever seen anyway.

62
00:05:36,405 --> 00:05:38,325
- Bertram.
- But they were good,

63
00:05:38,408 --> 00:05:40,327
- real good.
- Come on, Bertram!

64
00:05:40,411 --> 00:05:43,289
And all I had was a plastic toy mitt
that my grandmother gave me...

65
00:05:43,373 --> 00:05:45,793
for my birthday when I was six.

66
00:05:45,876 --> 00:05:50,132
But when I finally got up enough guts to
go out there and try and make friends,

67
00:05:50,215 --> 00:05:53,845
I found out that they never kept score,
they never chose sides,

68
00:05:53,886 --> 00:05:56,223
they never even really
stopped playing the game.

69
00:05:56,264 --> 00:06:00,812
It just went on forever.
Every day they picked up where
they left off the day before.

70
00:06:00,937 --> 00:06:03,899
- It was like an endless dream game.
- Come on! Come on!

71
00:06:04,025 --> 00:06:07,028
There was only eight of them,
so they didn't have a whole team.

72
00:06:07,070 --> 00:06:10,992
So even though I didn't know
how to play, I figured
I could be the ninth man...

73
00:06:11,117 --> 00:06:14,288
and maybe just stand in the outfield
somewhere and take up space.

74
00:06:14,371 --> 00:06:18,126
- Squints!
- Of course, if I'd have known what was
gonna happen when I got there,

75
00:06:18,210 --> 00:06:22,715
- I got it!
- I probably never would've gone.

76
00:06:22,882 --> 00:06:24,551
- Nice catch.
- Yeah.

77
00:06:30,726 --> 00:06:34,856
- Come on!
- [ Rustling ]

78
00:06:34,940 --> 00:06:38,152
[ Dog Barking ]

79
00:06:38,277 --> 00:06:41,990
[ Clattering, Banging ]

80
00:06:43,117 --> 00:06:44,953
[ Growling ]

81
00:06:53,255 --> 00:06:56,259
Come on, Benny,
hit a homer!

82
00:06:56,384 --> 00:06:58,303
- Come on!
- Hey, batter, batter, batter!

83
00:06:58,428 --> 00:07:00,598
- Whoa!
- Watch out!

84
00:07:00,723 --> 00:07:03,018
[ Boys Shouting ]

85
00:07:06,314 --> 00:07:10,444
- [ Screams ]
- [ All Laughing ]

86
00:07:21,291 --> 00:07:23,920
Okay, I'll get it!
Get it.

87
00:07:24,003 --> 00:07:28,300
Don't be a goofus. Don't be a goofus!
Don't be a goofus!

88
00:07:31,346 --> 00:07:33,516
[Rumbling Sound, Dog Growling]

89
00:07:36,853 --> 00:07:41,109
- Throw the ball back! Come on!
- Yeah, hurry up!

90
00:07:44,780 --> 00:07:46,532
[Barking]

91
00:07:51,956 --> 00:07:54,084
We are waiting!

92
00:07:54,209 --> 00:07:56,128
Come on! Throw it!

93
00:07:56,295 --> 00:07:58,506
[Boys Shouting]

94
00:07:58,590 --> 00:08:01,302
[ Shouting Continues ]

95
00:08:01,343 --> 00:08:05,056
- Come on, toss me the ball!
- Come on!

96
00:08:05,182 --> 00:08:07,101
Come on!

97
00:08:10,188 --> 00:08:12,650
[ Boys Laughing ]

98
00:08:12,691 --> 00:08:17,197
- Oh, my God!
- [ Laughing Continues ]

99
00:08:18,949 --> 00:08:20,994
My life's over.

100
00:08:21,036 --> 00:08:23,539
Did you see that hand?

101
00:08:23,706 --> 00:08:27,127
[Boys Chattering, Laughing]

102
00:08:27,168 --> 00:08:29,088
[Man Narrating]
If it wasn't for Benny,

103
00:08:29,171 --> 00:08:31,883
I never would've made
a single friend that summer,

104
00:08:31,966 --> 00:08:34,553
'cause all the rest of those
guys thought I was a lost cause.

105
00:08:35,930 --> 00:08:38,433
- Even before we became friends,
- [ Mechanical Whirring ]

106
00:08:38,517 --> 00:08:43,022
Benny and me were connected, connected
for the one moment later that summer...

107
00:08:43,106 --> 00:08:45,108
when I'd get us all
into the biggest pickle...

108
00:08:45,192 --> 00:08:47,987
any of us had ever seen.

109
00:08:53,703 --> 00:08:55,580
[ Knocking ]

110
00:08:55,705 --> 00:08:58,209
Night, hon.
[ Grunts ]

111
00:08:58,376 --> 00:09:01,838
Oh, I'm sorry, Mom.
It was an accident.

112
00:09:11,226 --> 00:09:14,480
Scotty, have you made
any friends yet?

113
00:09:16,107 --> 00:09:18,527
- No.
- Why not, honey?

114
00:09:20,613 --> 00:09:22,574
'Cause I'm still new.

115
00:09:22,699 --> 00:09:26,913
I don't want you sitting around in here
all summer fiddling with this stuff...

116
00:09:27,079 --> 00:09:29,082
like you did last summer
and the one before.

117
00:09:29,207 --> 00:09:31,669
I know you're smart,
and I'm proud of you.

118
00:09:31,752 --> 00:09:36,342
I want you to get out into the fresh air
and make some friends.

119
00:09:36,425 --> 00:09:39,846
Run around,
scrape your knees, get dirty.

120
00:09:39,929 --> 00:09:41,849
Climb trees, hop fences.

121
00:09:41,932 --> 00:09:45,228
Get into trouble,
for crying out loud.

122
00:09:45,311 --> 00:09:48,274
Not too much, but some.
You have my permission.

123
00:09:48,441 --> 00:09:51,903
How many mothers do you know who
say something like that to their sons?

124
00:09:51,987 --> 00:09:54,699
[ Chuckles ]
Well, none mothers, I guess.

125
00:09:54,782 --> 00:09:59,455
Honey, I want you to make
some friends this summer. Lots of them.

126
00:10:00,581 --> 00:10:02,500
Yeah, I know.

127
00:10:02,626 --> 00:10:04,545
But I'm not good
at anything, Mom.

128
00:10:04,586 --> 00:10:06,506
Face it,
I'm just an egghead.

129
00:10:06,631 --> 00:10:11,053
Honey, you'll always be just an egghead
with an attitude like that.

130
00:10:22,109 --> 00:10:25,071
[TV: Indistinct]

131
00:10:27,616 --> 00:10:29,786
[ Whispering ]
Well?

132
00:10:31,538 --> 00:10:33,874
Well?

133
00:10:33,958 --> 00:10:37,671
- He's too busy, Mom.
- Oh, no, honey, he's not.
He has some time.

134
00:10:37,796 --> 00:10:40,884
You go on back out there
and ask him.

135
00:10:41,009 --> 00:10:42,928
[TV Continues ]

136
00:10:43,011 --> 00:10:45,097
- Uh, Bill, uh--
- Yeah?

137
00:10:45,181 --> 00:10:48,393
I mean, Dad, uh, can we--

138
00:10:48,518 --> 00:10:52,857
I mean, could you, like you said,
teach me to play catch?

139
00:10:52,941 --> 00:10:55,277
Yeah. Sure.

140
00:10:55,361 --> 00:10:57,280
But I gotta get
this done, okay?

141
00:10:57,363 --> 00:10:59,866
- Okay, thanks.
- All right.

142
00:11:00,033 --> 00:11:01,869
- Bill?
- Yeah?

143
00:11:01,953 --> 00:11:05,540
Uh, couldn't you take a break
and teach him now?

144
00:11:05,707 --> 00:11:07,960
- Mom, it's okay, really.
- Honey,

145
00:11:08,127 --> 00:11:10,547
I said I would, and I will,
but I'm under the gun here.

146
00:11:10,630 --> 00:11:12,842
How long could it take?

147
00:11:13,009 --> 00:11:15,387
Can't you spare half an hour
and show him now?

148
00:11:15,470 --> 00:11:18,015
- Mom, really, it's okay.
- All right.

149
00:11:19,767 --> 00:11:22,396
Okay. I'll get my glove.

150
00:11:25,692 --> 00:11:29,238
See? I told you.

151
00:11:29,363 --> 00:11:31,533
Oh, great.

152
00:11:31,699 --> 00:11:34,119
All right, Scotty, get down
to that end of the yard.

153
00:11:34,203 --> 00:11:35,788
Okay.

154
00:11:35,871 --> 00:11:38,500
Now, the key to this game
is keeping your eye on the ball.

155
00:11:38,625 --> 00:11:42,213
No matter whether you're in the field
or at bat, eye on the ball, okay?

156
00:11:42,338 --> 00:11:44,383
All right. Uh, yeah.
I think so.

157
00:11:44,508 --> 00:11:46,969
Where the ball goes,
your glove should go. Got it?

158
00:11:47,053 --> 00:11:48,847
Okay.

159
00:11:48,972 --> 00:11:50,849
Okay. All right.

160
00:11:52,268 --> 00:11:54,688
[ Grunts ]

161
00:11:54,771 --> 00:11:57,274
Darn. Sorry.

162
00:11:57,399 --> 00:11:59,193
It's all right.
All right.

163
00:12:07,454 --> 00:12:10,041
Um-- Uh, here.

164
00:12:12,627 --> 00:12:14,547
Okay.

165
00:12:14,588 --> 00:12:16,674
Okay, I'm ready.

166
00:12:16,800 --> 00:12:20,513
Eye on the ball, okay?
Got it?

167
00:12:20,638 --> 00:12:21,848
Okay.

168
00:12:21,973 --> 00:12:24,685
If the ball moves,
move your glove. Got it?

169
00:12:24,810 --> 00:12:26,187
Yeah.

170
00:12:26,312 --> 00:12:28,690
All right. Here we go.

171
00:12:34,030 --> 00:12:36,826
Okay. You just need a bigger glove.
Throw it back to me this time.

172
00:12:39,579 --> 00:12:41,415
Throw it back.

173
00:12:56,810 --> 00:12:59,939
Okay. Scotty,
keep your eye on the ball.

174
00:13:00,022 --> 00:13:02,359
Okay. Got it.

175
00:13:02,442 --> 00:13:03,735
Okay.

176
00:13:05,237 --> 00:13:07,574
Ow! Oh, my eye!

177
00:13:07,699 --> 00:13:10,828
Ow! Ow! Oh!

178
00:13:10,953 --> 00:13:12,872
Ow! Ow!

179
00:13:12,914 --> 00:13:16,168
- What happened?
- [ Groans ] My eye.

180
00:13:16,252 --> 00:13:19,214
- Honey, get some ice. Ice.
- No, I got it.

181
00:13:19,339 --> 00:13:21,258
- Here you go.
- Those were for dinner.

182
00:13:21,383 --> 00:13:23,302
- Oh!
-Just hold it up there.

183
00:13:23,344 --> 00:13:25,263
Nice and hard.
Press it against-- Yeah.

184
00:13:25,388 --> 00:13:28,226
- I just took my eye off the ball, Mom.
- Yeah, but you caught it.

185
00:13:28,267 --> 00:13:30,979
- [Groaning]
-Just keep that on for, like, an hour.

186
00:13:31,146 --> 00:13:34,025
It'll still be black,
but it won't swell.

187
00:13:34,150 --> 00:13:36,570
Sorry.

188
00:13:36,737 --> 00:13:38,948
Gotta watch out
for that curve.

189
00:13:40,950 --> 00:13:42,786
[ Crying ]

190
00:13:45,915 --> 00:13:47,793
Hey.

191
00:13:50,671 --> 00:13:53,800
I'm gonna play some ball.
We need an extra guy. You wanna go?

192
00:13:53,967 --> 00:13:57,388
- No. Thanks.
- Why not? Don't you like baseball?

193
00:13:57,472 --> 00:13:59,892
- Oh, yeah, but--
- But what?

194
00:14:02,395 --> 00:14:05,107
But my glove--
it's busted.

195
00:14:05,190 --> 00:14:09,571
Uh, see? Now I can't go.
Thanks, though.

196
00:14:09,696 --> 00:14:11,490
It's okay.

197
00:14:12,700 --> 00:14:14,577
I got an extra one.

198
00:14:16,705 --> 00:14:18,666
Come on. Let's go.

199
00:14:21,545 --> 00:14:23,881
Mom, I'm gonna go
play some ball!

200
00:14:24,006 --> 00:14:25,925
I'll be back
in a little while.

201
00:14:26,050 --> 00:14:27,886
Come on. Let's go.

202
00:14:30,848 --> 00:14:33,727
- And I'm Babe Ruth.
- [Boys Chattering]

203
00:14:41,279 --> 00:14:43,865
Listen. Ready?

204
00:14:43,990 --> 00:14:46,494
Check this out.

205
00:14:46,619 --> 00:14:48,955
[ Muffled ]
I'm the Great Bambino.

206
00:14:49,039 --> 00:14:51,166
[ Boys ]
What?

207
00:14:51,292 --> 00:14:54,254
- I'm the Great Bambino.
- [ All ] What?

208
00:14:54,337 --> 00:14:56,590
I'm the Great Bambino.

209
00:14:56,715 --> 00:14:58,676
[ All ]
Oh!

210
00:14:58,718 --> 00:15:00,595
Who's that?

211
00:15:04,600 --> 00:15:06,520
What?

212
00:15:06,603 --> 00:15:09,524
[Scotty Narrating] I had no idea
who they were talking about.

213
00:15:09,565 --> 00:15:13,195
- What did he say?
- What, were you born in a barn, man?

214
00:15:13,362 --> 00:15:15,239
Yeah, what planet
are you from?

215
00:15:15,364 --> 00:15:17,659
[Scotty Narrating] But there was
no way I could let them know.

216
00:15:17,701 --> 00:15:19,954
You never heard
of the Sultan of Swat?

217
00:15:20,079 --> 00:15:21,998
The Titan of Terror?

218
00:15:22,040 --> 00:15:25,169
- The Colossus of Clout?
- The Colossus of Clout!

219
00:15:25,294 --> 00:15:28,924
- The King of Crash, man.
- [Scotty Narrating] So I lied.

220
00:15:29,007 --> 00:15:32,428
Oh, yeah, the Great Bambino.
Of course.

221
00:15:32,512 --> 00:15:34,389
I thought you said,
"the Great Bambi."

222
00:15:34,556 --> 00:15:36,642
That wimpy deer?

223
00:15:36,767 --> 00:15:40,105
Yeah. I guess. Sorry.

224
00:15:42,900 --> 00:15:48,282
Anyway, Scott, that's
Timmy and Tommy Timmons,

225
00:15:48,407 --> 00:15:50,827
Mike "Squints" Palledorous,

226
00:15:50,911 --> 00:15:53,455
Alan McClellan--
we call him Yeah-Yeah--

227
00:15:53,539 --> 00:15:56,084
Bertram Grover Weeks,

228
00:15:56,251 --> 00:15:58,671
Kenny DeNunez
and Hamilton Porter.

229
00:15:58,754 --> 00:16:01,257
We call him Ham.
Guys, this is Scott Smalls.

230
00:16:01,299 --> 00:16:03,260
Hi.

231
00:16:05,096 --> 00:16:08,934
Yeah, um, wel I, he's gonna play with us
'cause he makes nine.

232
00:16:09,017 --> 00:16:12,313
Now we've got a whole team. We're
wasting time. Let's go to the sandlot.

233
00:16:12,397 --> 00:16:15,192
- Benny, it's 9:00 in the morning.
- It's 9:00.

234
00:16:15,317 --> 00:16:16,569
- Why'd you bring him, Benny?
- 'Cause there's eight of us,
and he makes nine.

235
00:16:16,569 --> 00:16:18,613
- Why'd you bring him, Benny?
- 'Cause there's eight of us,
and he makes nine.

236
00:16:18,697 --> 00:16:21,283
Yeah, yeah, so would my sister,
but I didn't bring her.

237
00:16:21,408 --> 00:16:24,037
With nine guys we've got
a whole team, Yeah-Yeah.

238
00:16:25,122 --> 00:16:28,918
No. With Elswenger
we had a whole team.

239
00:16:29,043 --> 00:16:32,506
- Elswenger could catch.
- And throw.

240
00:16:32,590 --> 00:16:35,218
Come on, Benny, man.
He ain't game.

241
00:16:35,343 --> 00:16:38,430
- You saw the way he threw.
- Yeah.

