278
00:19:04,662 --> 00:19:07,374
Come on. Throw it in.

279
00:19:07,457 --> 00:19:10,336
What the hell's he doing?

280
00:19:14,132 --> 00:19:16,052
I don't believe this.

281
00:19:19,473 --> 00:19:22,393
Here. Sorry. Sorry.

282
00:19:49,094 --> 00:19:50,930
You can throw it, you know.

283
00:19:53,475 --> 00:19:55,352
No.

284
00:19:55,436 --> 00:19:57,522
I can't.

285
00:19:57,647 --> 00:19:59,525
I don't know how.

286
00:20:01,444 --> 00:20:05,574
Thanks for taking me here,
but I think I'd better go.

287
00:20:05,741 --> 00:20:08,703
Hey, hey.
You think too much.

288
00:20:08,787 --> 00:20:10,706
I bet you get straight A's
and shit, huh?

289
00:20:10,789 --> 00:20:13,126
No, I got a "B" once.

290
00:20:13,292 --> 00:20:16,588
Actually an A-minus.
But it should've been a "B."

291
00:20:16,713 --> 00:20:19,384
Man, this is baseball.
You gotta stop thinking.

292
00:20:19,467 --> 00:20:21,386
You just have fun.

293
00:20:21,470 --> 00:20:24,390
I mean, if you were having fun,
you would've caught that ball.

294
00:20:27,644 --> 00:20:29,480
You ever have
a paper route?

295
00:20:29,605 --> 00:20:31,691
I helped a guy once.

296
00:20:33,360 --> 00:20:36,197
Okay. Well, chuck it like
you would throw a paper.

297
00:20:36,322 --> 00:20:39,618
When your arm gets here,
just let go.

298
00:20:39,702 --> 00:20:41,579
Just let go.
It's that easy.

299
00:20:42,831 --> 00:20:45,543
How do I catch it?

300
00:20:47,503 --> 00:20:51,133
Just stand there and stick your glove
out in the air.

301
00:20:51,217 --> 00:20:53,177
I'll take care of it.

302
00:20:53,219 --> 00:20:56,390
About time, Benny.
My clothes are going out of style.

303
00:20:56,515 --> 00:20:59,227
- They already are, Squints.
- Shut up!

304
00:21:00,270 --> 00:21:02,189
I told you, Benny.

305
00:21:04,818 --> 00:21:06,737
Smalls, throw it to second.

306
00:21:06,862 --> 00:21:09,282
Okay.

307
00:21:09,365 --> 00:21:11,201
[ Groans ]

308
00:21:11,368 --> 00:21:13,704
- Not again.
- [ Spits ]

309
00:21:13,787 --> 00:21:15,874
We're wasting time, Benny.

310
00:21:17,542 --> 00:21:19,420
Please catch it.

311
00:21:27,806 --> 00:21:29,892
Please catch it.

312
00:21:30,017 --> 00:21:32,645
Please catch it.
Please catch it.

313
00:21:39,738 --> 00:21:41,657
Yeah!

314
00:21:43,618 --> 00:21:47,665
- All right!
- He's all right.

315
00:21:47,790 --> 00:21:50,377
I told you so, man.

316
00:21:54,757 --> 00:21:56,676
Okay.

317
00:21:56,760 --> 00:21:59,805
- Let's play some ball.
- Yeah, let's play some ball.

318
00:21:59,889 --> 00:22:03,352
All right.
I knew it... all the time.

319
00:22:07,107 --> 00:22:08,859
Yeah!

320
00:22:08,942 --> 00:22:11,112
[Dog Growling]

321
00:22:11,195 --> 00:22:14,074
[Fence Rattling]

322
00:22:15,743 --> 00:22:17,662
[ Gasps ]

323
00:22:24,337 --> 00:22:26,423
I'll show you some more
tomorrow, okay?

324
00:22:26,507 --> 00:22:28,426
- Okay. Bye.
- You did good.

325
00:22:28,468 --> 00:22:30,387
See you later, Ham.
8:00 tomorrow.

326
00:22:30,512 --> 00:22:32,431
- 8:00, Benny?
- Yeah. See you later, Smalls.

327
00:22:32,473 --> 00:22:34,893
Bye. See you tomorrow.

328
00:22:34,934 --> 00:22:36,854
Benny, wait!

329
00:22:36,979 --> 00:22:40,650
- Your glove.
- Keep it, man.

330
00:22:40,817 --> 00:22:42,694
Thanks!

331
00:22:44,280 --> 00:22:46,574
Oh, yeah.
Hey, Smalls.

332
00:22:51,289 --> 00:22:55,586
Um, bring a T-shirt
and jeans tomorrow, okay?

333
00:22:55,711 --> 00:22:59,508
- Oh, um, you got a fireplace?
- Oh, yeah.

334
00:22:59,591 --> 00:23:01,511
Yeah, why?

335
00:23:01,636 --> 00:23:03,471
Throw that hat
in there, man.

336
00:23:03,597 --> 00:23:06,475
Oh, yeah. You know,
it was the only one I had.

337
00:23:06,559 --> 00:23:09,020
Not anymore.
Wear my old hat.

338
00:23:09,104 --> 00:23:11,023
8:00 tomorrow morning.

339
00:23:11,106 --> 00:23:14,527
Thanks, Benny.
Great. 8:00.

340
00:23:16,613 --> 00:23:18,449
Mom, guess what?

341
00:23:34,303 --> 00:23:37,891
- Hamilton "The Babe" Porter.
- [ Chuckles ]

342
00:23:37,974 --> 00:23:40,353
"Long-ball" Porter.

343
00:23:40,436 --> 00:23:42,313
Come on, DeNunez.

344
00:23:43,690 --> 00:23:47,862
[ All Laughing, Taunting ]

345
00:23:48,029 --> 00:23:51,492
Yeah, okay.
Yes, I see it. Yes.

346
00:23:51,534 --> 00:23:54,454
[ Boys Shouting ]

347
00:23:56,874 --> 00:23:58,793
- Whoa!
- [Boys Laughing]

348
00:23:58,835 --> 00:24:01,880
You call that pitching?

349
00:24:02,047 --> 00:24:04,801
This is baseball,
not tennis.

350
00:24:04,884 --> 00:24:07,262
- Give him a tennis racket.
- Give me something to hit.

351
00:24:07,346 --> 00:24:09,599
All right, Ham.
This is my heater.

352
00:24:09,724 --> 00:24:13,020
- I dare you to hit it.
- You'll be sorry.

353
00:24:13,103 --> 00:24:15,648
- Give that boy a bigger bat.
- You want the heater,
I'll give it to you.

354
00:24:15,732 --> 00:24:18,318
Give him a basketball.
Maybe then he'll hit it.

355
00:24:23,283 --> 00:24:25,453
- [Clattering]
- Oh, man!

356
00:24:25,536 --> 00:24:28,749
Yeah!
That's how you do it.

357
00:24:30,835 --> 00:24:33,380
Ham, you idiot.
Now we can't play no more.

358
00:24:33,421 --> 00:24:35,633
Great, you idiot!

359
00:24:35,716 --> 00:24:38,595
Hit me with the heater.

360
00:24:38,636 --> 00:24:40,848
Stupid idiot!

361
00:24:40,889 --> 00:24:43,977
Low and outside.
Just like I like it.

362
00:24:55,074 --> 00:24:56,994
I'm gonna hit you!

363
00:24:57,035 --> 00:25:02,125
- Wait a sec. I'll get it.
- [Ham] 1932 called shot
World Series by The Babe.

364
00:25:02,250 --> 00:25:04,921
Called shot by the Babe.

365
00:25:05,004 --> 00:25:07,173
No!

366
00:25:07,299 --> 00:25:10,887
[ All ]
No!

367
00:25:11,012 --> 00:25:13,432
[Boys Shouting]

368
00:25:16,352 --> 00:25:19,982
- Smalls, come back!
- Hey guys, I'll get it!

369
00:25:20,107 --> 00:25:22,443
- Smalls!
- Smalls!

370
00:25:22,610 --> 00:25:25,572
- What are you doing?
- Smalls, wait!

371
00:25:25,739 --> 00:25:28,409
- Guys, what are you--
- [ All ] Smalls!

372
00:25:28,451 --> 00:25:31,038
Get off!
Guys, I gotta get the ball!

373
00:25:31,121 --> 00:25:35,210
- No, wait!
- Get off of me! Now!

374
00:25:35,252 --> 00:25:37,171
- You're gonna get yourself killed!
- Killed, man, jeez!

375
00:25:37,296 --> 00:25:39,215
Stop!

376
00:25:41,301 --> 00:25:43,387
Holy crap,
you could've been killed.

377
00:25:43,429 --> 00:25:45,640
Yeah, yeah, truly.
What are you doing?

378
00:25:45,723 --> 00:25:48,602
You guys were leaving,
so I just thought I'd hop the fence--

379
00:25:48,644 --> 00:25:52,274
- If you were thinking, you
wouldn't have thought that.
- You can't go back there.

380
00:25:52,315 --> 00:25:54,735
- Then how do we get the ball back?
- We don't.

381
00:25:54,777 --> 00:25:56,696
- We don't.
- It's history.

382
00:25:56,821 --> 00:26:00,409
- It's history. Kiss it--
- Kiss it good-bye. Shut up, Tommy.

383
00:26:00,451 --> 00:26:02,954
It's gone, man. Gone.

384
00:26:03,079 --> 00:26:06,542
Game's over, man.
We'll just get another ball tomorrow.

385
00:26:06,667 --> 00:26:09,129
- Yeah.
- We'll never see it again.

386
00:26:09,254 --> 00:26:11,966
Why not?

387
00:26:15,345 --> 00:26:17,306
[ All ]
The Beast.

388
00:26:17,389 --> 00:26:19,434
What is that?

389
00:26:24,607 --> 00:26:26,443
Smalls, listen to me.

390
00:26:28,362 --> 00:26:32,367
Go to that fence... real slow,
and be quiet.

391
00:26:32,451 --> 00:26:35,121
- But... I-I think--
- No, no, no. No, no.

392
00:26:35,163 --> 00:26:37,791
-Just go and peek through that hole.
- But I--

393
00:26:37,958 --> 00:26:41,796
-But I saw something. What's back there?
-It's okay. Just go.

394
00:26:41,963 --> 00:26:44,341
-Just go.
- Go, Smalls.

395
00:26:44,425 --> 00:26:46,302
Come on, Smalls.

396
00:26:48,179 --> 00:26:51,058
[ All ]
Shh!

397
00:26:54,145 --> 00:26:56,065
[Boys Whispering]

398
00:27:01,613 --> 00:27:03,533
Shh!

399
00:27:08,372 --> 00:27:12,211
- Shh!
- Be quiet.

400
00:27:14,088 --> 00:27:17,092
- [ Growling ]
- [ Gasps ]

401
00:27:17,175 --> 00:27:19,094
Something got the ball.

402
00:27:21,139 --> 00:27:23,225
W-What was that thing?

403
00:27:24,518 --> 00:27:26,354
[ All ]
Camp out.

404
00:27:26,521 --> 00:27:29,900
# In the jungle
the mighty jungle #

405
00:27:29,984 --> 00:27:34,239
# The lion sleeps tonight ##

406
00:27:34,406 --> 00:27:36,242
[Scotty]
Hey, guys, sorry I'm late.

407
00:27:36,409 --> 00:27:38,244
- My mom made me put on my jacket,
- Shut up!

408
00:27:38,411 --> 00:27:40,539
- and then she made me do the dishes.
- [ Boys Laughing]

409
00:27:40,706 --> 00:27:43,835
Your poor little mommy
made you do the big bad dishes.

410
00:27:43,960 --> 00:27:47,715
- Hey, you want a s'more?
- Some more what?

411
00:27:47,840 --> 00:27:50,218
- No, no, you want a s'more?
- [Boys Chattering]

412
00:27:50,302 --> 00:27:54,807
I haven't had anything yet,
so how can I have some more of nothing?

413
00:27:54,933 --> 00:27:57,770
- Shut up!
- You're killing me, Smalls.

414
00:27:57,811 --> 00:28:01,066
- All right. Who cut one?
- These are s'mores stuff.

415
00:28:01,232 --> 00:28:04,195
- Okay, pay attention.
- Bertram!

416
00:28:04,236 --> 00:28:06,489
First you take the graham.

417
00:28:06,614 --> 00:28:10,244
You stick the chocolate
on the graham.

418
00:28:10,369 --> 00:28:13,457
- Then you roast the 'mallow.
- No, it's my sleeping bag.

419
00:28:13,582 --> 00:28:16,002
When the 'mallow's flaming,

420
00:28:16,085 --> 00:28:18,588
Yes, it is yours.
It has a yellow stain on it.

421
00:28:18,713 --> 00:28:20,966
you stick it
on the chocolate.

422
00:28:21,092 --> 00:28:23,428
- You're gonna set the place on fire.
- Then...

423
00:28:23,511 --> 00:28:26,432
- you cover it with the other end.
- Make me one of those.

424
00:28:26,515 --> 00:28:28,434
Yeah, me too.

425
00:28:28,518 --> 00:28:32,106
- Then you stuff.
- I don't like that chocolate stuff.

426
00:28:32,273 --> 00:28:34,275
Kind of messy, but good.
Try some.

427
00:28:34,442 --> 00:28:37,029
Okay. Quiet, you guys.

428
00:28:37,112 --> 00:28:40,367
- [ Chattering ]
- Shh! Shh!

429
00:28:40,450 --> 00:28:43,412
Quiet! Are you trying
to wake it up?

430
00:28:43,454 --> 00:28:46,041
It just went to bed.

431
00:28:46,207 --> 00:28:49,003
- What just went to bed?
- [ Boys ] Shh!

432
00:28:49,128 --> 00:28:51,423
The Beast.

433
00:28:51,548 --> 00:28:54,093
- Oh, yeah!
- Shh!

434
00:28:54,218 --> 00:28:56,137
-Jeez.
- Dang.

435
00:28:56,262 --> 00:28:58,348
Shh.

436
00:28:59,433 --> 00:29:01,477
Now quiet.

437
00:29:03,438 --> 00:29:08,653
The legend of The Beast
goes back a long time...

438
00:29:09,988 --> 00:29:13,618
before any of us
could even pick up a baseball.

439
00:29:15,329 --> 00:29:20,126
Back to a place
called Mertle's Acres.

440
00:29:20,252 --> 00:29:25,133
It all started about, mmm,
20 years ago,

441
00:29:25,258 --> 00:29:29,096
when thieves kept stealing junk
from Mertle's Acres junkyard.

442
00:29:29,180 --> 00:29:32,601
So Mr. Mertle, the guy
that used to own the place,

443
00:29:32,684 --> 00:29:36,564
got him this new pup
from the dog pound.

444
00:29:36,690 --> 00:29:38,776
He fed him whole sides of beef...

445
00:29:38,942 --> 00:29:41,529
and turned the pup loose
in the junkyard.

446
00:29:41,613 --> 00:29:43,907
And the pup was grateful.

447
00:29:49,456 --> 00:29:51,584
[ Thunderous Footsteps ]

448
00:29:55,422 --> 00:29:58,843
And so, in a few weeks,
the pup grew into The Beast.

449
00:29:58,968 --> 00:30:02,473
And he grew big,
and he grew mean...

450
00:30:02,598 --> 00:30:06,770
so that he could protect the junkyard
with only one thing on his mind:

451
00:30:06,854 --> 00:30:09,482
to kill everyone
that broke in.

452
00:30:09,607 --> 00:30:14,071
- And he did, and he liked it a lot!
- [ Men Screaming ]

453
00:30:14,155 --> 00:30:17,951
The Beast was the most perfect
junkyard dog that ever lived.

454
00:30:17,993 --> 00:30:21,164
A true killing machine.

455
00:30:21,289 --> 00:30:24,126
But after a while, the cops started
getting phone calls from people...

456
00:30:24,210 --> 00:30:26,963
reporting all the missing thieves,

457
00:30:27,047 --> 00:30:29,341
the ones The Beast had killed.

458
00:30:29,425 --> 00:30:32,178
It added up to about 120--

459
00:30:32,345 --> 00:30:34,598
173 guys.

460
00:30:34,681 --> 00:30:36,767
- It's true.
- [ Growling ]

461
00:30:36,851 --> 00:30:39,229
They never found a single body.

462
00:30:39,312 --> 00:30:42,441
Not one. Some people say
they all got away.

463
00:30:42,525 --> 00:30:45,279
But we all know
what really happened.

464
00:30:45,404 --> 00:30:47,365
The Beast ate them.

465
00:30:47,448 --> 00:30:51,286
He ate them bone and all.

466
00:30:51,370 --> 00:30:53,706
The Beast was too good
at his guard dog job,

467
00:30:53,790 --> 00:30:56,501
so the police said
he had to be retired.

468
00:30:56,543 --> 00:30:59,380
My grandpa, Squidman Palledorous,

469
00:30:59,505 --> 00:31:01,758
was police chiefback then.

470
00:31:01,883 --> 00:31:06,431
He ordered Mr. Mertle to turn
his backyard into a fortress...

471
00:31:06,514 --> 00:31:09,977
and chain up The Beast
and put him under the house...

472
00:31:10,102 --> 00:31:13,106
where he could never get out
to eat children and stuff.

473
00:31:13,231 --> 00:31:15,985
- That's where he's been for 20 years.
- [ Growling ]

474
00:31:16,068 --> 00:31:18,822
And that's where he'll be
for the rest of his life.

475
00:31:18,947 --> 00:31:21,951
Because Mr. Mertle
asked the cops how long...

476
00:31:22,076 --> 00:31:24,621
he had to keep The Beast
chained up like a slave,

477
00:31:24,788 --> 00:31:29,127
they said until forever.

478
00:31:29,210 --> 00:31:31,213
Forever. Forever.

479
00:31:31,213 --> 00:31:33,675
Forever. Forever.

480
00:31:33,758 --> 00:31:37,471
Forever.
[ Echoing ]

481
00:31:37,596 --> 00:31:42,019
And so, The Beast sits there
under that lean-to,

482
00:31:42,102 --> 00:31:46,441
dreaming of the time when he can
break the chain and get out,

483
00:31:46,608 --> 00:31:50,196
dreaming of the time
he can chase and kill again.

484
00:31:51,448 --> 00:31:53,492
See, man? That's why
you can't go over there.

485
00:31:53,575 --> 00:31:56,287
Nobody ever has.
Nobody ever will.

486
00:31:56,371 --> 00:31:59,625
